oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Women aboard rail car
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Motor car in the Doe River Gorge at Pardue Point on the East Tennessee and Western North Carolina Railroad, with 4 people aboard. Two women sit behind the man, while one woman stands. All the women have kerchiefs in hair.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
